video:video.video:title: Welcome to Chaotic (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In the first episode of the series, the protagonist, Tom Majors, receives his access code for Chaotic, a place where, according to his best friend, Kaz, you can turn into the Creatures and play for real.

video:video.video:title: Welcome to Chaotic (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In continuation of the series, after entering his access code, the protagonist, Tom Majors, discovers that all the fantasies of his friend’s, Kaz, were real and has his first battle in Chaotic

video:video.video:title: Unexpected
video:video.video:description: In this episode we meet the fourth member of the group, Peyton, and his… “eccentric”, personality.

video:video.video:title: Over Under Rent Asunder
video:video.video:description: The ancient war between Good versus Evil in the Chaotic universe: OverWorld vs. UnderWorld.

video:video.video:title: Crash Course
video:video.video:description: In this episode, Kaz faces Klay in a dispute while Tom tries to get the scan of a lunatic Creature whose life is playing tricks.

video:video.video:title: The Thing About Bodal
video:video.video:description: In this episode we meet Bodal, a Creature (very) talkative and adorably annoying and cocky about himself, and also see the most improbable of all fights in Chaotic.

video:video.video:title: Buggin' Out
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll know another of the four Tribes in Chaotic, the Danians, a Tribe formed by insects of all kinds that take the safety of their domains seriously, especially when it comes to Chaotic players.

video:video.video:title: Everything's in Flux
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll know a little more about Krystella, a player as unprincipled as Klay that does everything, no matter what, to succeed or to prevent those who cross her path to succeed themselves.

video:video.video:title: Castle Bodhran or Bust (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet the story of Reginald Terrington, the problems in which he got himself and the friends group’s attempt to rescue him with a bet that could mean the end of career in Chaotic of one of them.

video:video.video:title: Castle Bodhran or Bust (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In the continuation of the previous episode, the protagonist, Tom Majors, comes face-to-face with his hero, but before he could even try to rescue Reggie, he must not only gain his trust, but also fight a real battle against another Tribe along with his friends.

video:video.video:title: Lord of Treachery
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet the treacherous Lord Van Bloot, second in command of the Underworld, and how Chaor makes of Kaz his spy and uses the Chaotic battles as a military strategy against him

video:video.video:title: Battledrome of the Sexes
video:video.video:description: In this espisódio we’ll discover (or not) who plays Chaotic better, men or women, boys or girls, in a fight between Peyton and Krystella.

video:video.video:title: Battle Lessons
video:video.video:description: In this episode, the protagonist, Tom Majors, finds out about the main event in Chaotic: The CodeMasters Matches!

video:video.video:title: The Birth of Borth-Majar
video:video.video:description: In this episode we will know the origins of an unusual creature, Borth-Majar, and how Kaz deals with his collective individually personality (what? O.o)

video:video.video:title: Shifting Sands
video:video.video:description: In this episode Peyton shows to Tom that not all of the Mipedians are cruel and pitiless as those he met while rescuing Reggie.

video:video.video:title: Fallen Hero
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a treacherous coup of Lord Van Bloot against Maxxor that could destroy the Otherworld.

video:video.video:title: Scavenger Scan
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Kaz and Peyton competing with each other (again) to see who is the best player of Chaotic between them.

video:video.video:title: Allmageddon
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll know the story of Hoton, a Creature that, seeking for an ancient power to protect everything and everyone he loved, ended up losing everything.

video:video.video:title: A Fearsome Fate
video:video.video:description: In the previous episodes, the protagonist, Tom Majors, finally got a new scan of his favorite Creature, Maxxor, but when he used it for the first time in battle he realizes that something is wrong.

video:video.video:title: Maze of Menace
video:video.video:description: In this episode, continuing the sequence in which the Commander of the Otherworld, Maxxor, was ambushed by Lord Van Bloot’s treacherous Mugic, we’ll see a partnership between Creatures and humans to restore the Fallen Hero before it’s too late.

video:video.video:title: Out in the Cold
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Kaz’s journey through a dangerous path, with an unusual guidance, to the aid of the reclusive Raimusa in the Crystal Range.

video:video.video:title: Chaotikings
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Kaz’s initiation in the most famous “club” in chaotic… or not.

video:video.video:title: Stelgar Strikes
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet Mommark, a mad scientist from the OverWorld, and one of his creations, Stelgar.

video:video.video:title: The CodeMaster Chronicles (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see the first part of the most amazing match in Chaotic: The battle between Tom Majors and the CodeMaster Crellan!

video:video.video:title: The CodeMaster Chronicles (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In continuation of the previous episode we’ll see the outcome of the epic battle. So epic that have almost no time for a proper prologue ^_^

video:video.video:title: The Ultimate Scan
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll know a bit about a mythical Creature called Iparu and its fantastic abilities.

video:video.video:title: An Easy Win
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see how things can get really ugly when we try to take advantage of a rookie, right Peyton? ^_^

video:video.video:title: A Flux Too Far
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Kaz and Peyton trying to get a scan of the Flux Bauble (or not).

video:video.video:title: Chaotic Crisis
video:video.video:description: In this episode, the Creatures of Chaotic invade Earth! Let’s get Chaotic… for our planet!

video:video.video:title: The Curse of Kor-Bek
video:video.video:description: In this episode, set in the archipelago in which Peyton and Kaz ended up in the episode “A Flux Too Far”, we’ll have pirates, buried treasures, curses and chasing.

video:video.video:title: Fire Fighters
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a hot fight, literally, in which both players will try to prove their own superiority as well as of one of of the Four Elements.

video:video.video:title: Chasm Quest
video:video.video:description: In this episode Tom finally decides to explore the Prexxor Chasm, in Perim, from the scan he got from CodeMaster Crellan, until he realizes that something is really wrong.

video:video.video:title: Train Wreck
video:video.video:description: In this episode, when Kaz starts getting trouble in chaotic, Peyton helps him with a… not very conventional personal trainer.

video:video.video:title: Trading Cards
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a card trading chain engineered by Sarah so she could have the scan of rare Mugic. Of course our gentlemen wouldn’t let her down… right?

video:video.video:title: Dual Duel (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Krystella and Klay up to no good (again), resulting in a interesting dual battle for the scan of a wicked Battlegear.

video:video.video:title: Dual Duel (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In the continuation of the previous episode we’ll not only see the ending of the battle in midst of Krystella and Klay’s mental games but we’ll see as well that… well… karma is a bitch ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

video:video.video:title: Going Under
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a small part of one of the most known teachings of Sun Tzu’s The Art of War in Chaotic: Know your enemy!

video:video.video:title: Big Time
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Sarah’s quest to get the scan of a rare and powerful winged Danian that ends up on her frustrating a kidnapping attempt by an enemy Tribe

video:video.video:title: Eye of the Maelstrom
video:video.video:description: In this episode, Tom and his friends will help Najarin and a group of Mipedians in a important mission and that trust is a gift, not a right

video:video.video:title: Fighting Friendly (Season Finale)
video:video.video:description: In this episode… the end! Of the season, of a promising career and of a long time friendship…

video:video.video:title: A Rare Hazard
video:video.video:description: In the first episode of the Second Season we will have a closure for events of the previous episode, with right to terrorism and espionage

video:video.video:title: Dangers of Diplomacy
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see that it’s easier to get ants with honey than with vinegar, but that too much honey might not be a very good idea either

video:video.video:title: The Floundering Father
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a blabbermouth knows-it-all father getting real after a quadruple challenge

video:video.video:title: Colosseum Showdown
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a little misunderstanding end up in a epic way in the best Real Steel style

video:video.video:title: Rockwave and Roll
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see a match between Peyton and his musical idol, with rights to a subtle tribute to one of KISS’ lead singer Gene Simmons

video:video.video:title: Chaor's Commandos (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see an elite squad led by Chaor in a bold raid to Kiru City towards the Overworld Arsenal

video:video.video:title: Chaor's Commandos (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In the continuation of the previous episode we’ll see Chaor’s invasion to the Overworld Arsenal in Kiru City

video:video.video:title: Mega Match
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see the internal competition between Kaz and Peyton to see who is the best Chaotic player get to a next level… only now it’s up to Tom

video:video.video:title: Time's Up
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll have a grayish, silent, “Futuresight” with a small and subtle spoiler of the Season’s apex

video:video.video:title: Gigantempopolis
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet Gigantempopolis, a desert place, full of mysteries, treasures and, of course, curses, in the best Lord of the Rings style.

video:video.video:title: War Beasts
video:video.video:description: In this episode, after a while without mess with other players, Krystella and Klay set up for Peyton to get the scan of a War Beast, a humongous Mipedian titan as powerful as lunatic and, apparently, uncontrollable

video:video.video:title: From the Deep (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode a mysterious Creature from a long forgotten past arises again with astonishing and disturbing revelations about the future of Perim

video:video.video:title: From the Deep (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In the continuation of the previous episode, betrayal, brainwash, military coup and the beginning of the end… Let the Invasion begin!

video:video.video:title: Tale of Two Toms
video:video.video:description: In this episode an easy going version of our protagonist comes into play and, thanks to an evil pushing, ends up in a fight, in the best Chaotic style

video:video.video:title: Blight Fight
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet Garv, the OverWorld Caretaker in charge of Lake Morn, helping Tom (and Smildon) to heal the Prexxor Chasm from the Blight instead of fighting it by brute-force

video:video.video:title: Newbie
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet Shinwan, an unyielding newcomer who gets the first M&rsquo;arrillian scan

video:video.video:title: Putting the Muge in Mugic
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll have a common (and unnecessary) territorial war complete with treason, sabotage, counter-espionage and lessons of leadership between OverWorlders and Mipedians

video:video.video:title: Mister E
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see more about the power of the M&rsquo;arrillians and the beginning of the possible future shown in “Time’s Up”

video:video.video:title: When a CodeMaster Calls
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Peyton going in a journey into M&rsquo;arrillian territory in name of CodeMaster Hotekk in order to become his apprentice… only not ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

video:video.video:title: Earth to Kaz
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Kaz’s passion for Chaotic becoming a problem for him when he needs to prove to the psychologist of his school that Chaotic is a real place O_O

video:video.video:title: Raznus Returns
video:video.video:description: In this episode, a problematic excavation leads some Mandiblors leaded by Odu-Bathax and Raznus, former OverWorld Ambassador to the Danians, now Assimilated, to the basement of the Arsenal of OverWorld

video:video.video:title: Warriors of Eternity
video:video.video:description: In this episode, Sarah is attacked by a Mipedian ghost and her friends, while searching for her, join a group of Mipedians who are searching for the legendary Owayki and his Stone Warriors, immune to the M&rsquo;arrillian’s mind control

video:video.video:title: UnderWorld Overthrown
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Chaor and his loyal fighters execute a battleplan against the M&rsquo;arrillians in the Marsh of Murk

video:video.video:title: Triple Threat
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see the Tribal Alliance overcoming its cultural differences so they united may have a chance against the M&rsquo;arrillians

video:video.video:title: Last Stand (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode, the beginning of the end… the battle for Perim is now!

video:video.video:title: Last Stand (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In this episode, the battle continues in different regions of Perim at once… and in the Tribal Alliance itself as well

video:video.video:title: Legions of Aa'une (Season Finale)
video:video.video:description: In this episode, the battle continues with overturns and some shifting… and the end!

video:video.video:title: Perithon!
video:video.video:description: In this episode, after an intense battle and glorious victory over the M&rsquo;arrillians, the Tribes decide to keep Tribal Alliance towards a prosperous Perim and, to celebrate the peace, they make a car race… but old habits die hard…

video:video.video:title: Worlds Apart
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet Jycella, Krystella’s twin sister, and we’ll see that the bad relationship between them, common among humans, also happens in Perim, with the twin sisters Aivenna and Nivenna

video:video.video:title: Kickin' Bot
video:video.video:description: In this episode, Perim’s Dr. Frankenstein decides to implement part of his own brain in the Gigantroopers, making them intelligent enough to try to takeover the Underworld, resulting in a battle in the best Pacific Rim style

video:video.video:title: Hotekk's Challenge (Part 1)
video:video.video:description: In this episode, Tom wins the seventh battle in the Hotekk Drome, and thus is challenged by the CodeMaster himself

video:video.video:title: Hotekk's Challenge (Part 2)
video:video.video:description: In this episode, after winning in a very intelligent way CodeMaster Hotekk, Tom gets very disappointed with his reward… until he and his friends discover that a desert and not very interesting Location is actually much more than it looks (really!)

video:video.video:title: Yesterday's Heroes
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet Vlar, a thief renegade by the ancient Perim’s OverWorld Tribe which, possibly, is Maxxor’s ancestor

video:video.video:title: Losers' Circle
video:video.video:description: In this episode, Kaz is so psyched with his new scans from ancient Perim he decides to challenge every player who defeated him, thinking nobody would stand a chance… until his archenemy proves him otherwise.

video:video.video:title: A Gigantic Mission
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll see Vlar guiding Kiru and his fighters through the Temple of the ancient Gigantempopolis, when the giants were alive, in an attempt of dissuade Kaal to not invade Kiru City anymore, however, during the trip, the own future of the OverWorld was traced

video:video.video:title: Threshold of Destruction
video:video.video:description: In this episode, once Dranakis Threshold’s secret leaked out, several players ported to ancient Perim, including Chaotic’s “Bonnie &amp; Clyde”, who didn’t take long in conspiring with an old acquaintance, making of a painful event become, potentially, irreversible.

video:video.video:title: A Peytonic Adventure
video:video.video:description: In this episode, an adventure in the 007 style in which Peyton is challenged by a world famous counterfeiter for a Chaotic match

video:video.video:title: Elementary
video:video.video:description: In this episode we’ll meet the four Elemental Servants of the Lost City and a battle in Chaotic with them all at once

video:video.video:title: Son of the Spiritlands
video:video.video:description: In this episode, an indestructible Creature from the Spiritlands threatens to destroy the whole Perim unless Tangath Toborn faces him.
